.TH "sysfs_ctlreg_write" 9 "sysfs_ctlreg_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sysfs_ctlreg_write \- Write method for writing to ctlreg
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" sysfs_ctlreg_write
.BI "(struct file *filp "  ","
.BI "struct kobject *kobj "  ","
.BI "struct bin_attribute *bin_attr "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ","
.BI "loff_t off "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "filp" 12
open sysfs file
.IP "kobj" 12
kernel kobject that contains the kernel class device.
.IP "bin_attr" 12
kernel attributes passed to us.
.IP "buf" 12
contains the data to be written to the adapter IOREG space.
.IP "off" 12
offset into buffer to beginning of data.
.IP "count" 12
bytes to transfer.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Accessed via /sys/class/scsi_host/hostxxx/ctlreg.
Uses the adapter io control registers to send buf contents to the adapter.
.SH "RETURN"
-ERANGE off and count combo out of range
-EINVAL off, count or buff address invalid
-EPERM adapter is offline
value of count, buf contents written
